    <string name="about_description">This app exists to provide a proof of concept for various encryption methods
        and password generators that are written in Java. </string>
    <string name="about_otp_head">One Time Pad</string>
    <string name="about_otp_description">BlackC4t One Time Pad (OTP) requires the use of a pre-shared key to encrypt
        plain text. OTP is a form of symmetric encryption (it is also proof of concept) and is therefore not recommended
        to be used as a primary form of encryption. </string>
    <string name="about_2kotp_head">Two Key One Time Pad (Shibe)</string>
    <string name="about_2kotp_description">Uses the One Time Pad encryption with 2 keys.</string>
    <string name="about_pke_head">Public Key Cryptography</string>
    <string name="about_pke_description">Uses a Modulus and Public Key to encrypt, and the Modulus and the Private
        Key to Decrypt Note that this is proof of concept. </string>
